name: A Beautiful Home From Home
description:
Charming, elegant and characterful apartment (sleeps 2, plus 2 children on the sofa-bed) in a secure period building right in the centre of London, only 200 yards from Oxford St and Soho, yards from Charlotte Street restaurants and bars.

The space
Fully equipped kitchen, comfortable and light lounge, tastefully furnished throughout. Access to a quiet roof terrace for sunbathing and dining.

An inspirational writers' retreat, in this apartment has been written a best-selling culinary guide (The Flavour Thesaurus, which you’ll find in the kitchen), an award-winning music score (for the hit US TV show House Of Cards, which you’ll find in the DVD/Blu-ray collection) and two acclaimed movie scripts (Let’s Be Evil and Kung Fu Princess), so it certainly seems to attract a string of talented guests, who find the space a convenient and creative oasis of calm amid the bustle of the city.

host_about:
I work in film, as Producer and Executive Producer (Killers Anonymous, The Machine, One Night In Bath, Clubbed, Romans 12:20, Kung Fu Princess, Let's Be Evil etc) and theatre (West End productions of The Railway Children, Guys 'n' Dolls etc).

We are a family of 7 (kids 25, 21, 10, 8, 2) and travel extensively, in the summer to the south of France/Corsica, every year to Venice, skiing in winter in the Alps, with the occasional foray to the States (LA, mostly) and the Far East (Thailand).

We always rent self-catering accommodation, so we trust we provide what we appreciate when we travel: places that are comfortable, extensively equipped, centrally located and into which you can settle down and feel 'at home' immediately upon arrival (never sterile nor soulless).

We can handle 'multi-stays' for European trips that involve visits to London, the British countryside, Bath and/or Venice. Please just enquire.

We have three apartments in the same building and we are Landlords of the block.

We look forward to welcoming you.

The space

The corridor leads you further along to a laundry room and toilet with sink. Further along is a brand new luxury kitchen, professionally designed with wood cabinetry, expensively outfitted with Miele appliances and a hot water tap. This space has epic proportions and lofty high ceilings with a dining table for up to ten guests, placed by the back patio doors which open on to a very large grassy garden. The garden has a traditional wood-burning pizza oven as well as a big trampoline which kids will love!

host_about:
LHA London has been providing high quality accommodation in London since 1940 – we celebrate our 75th Anniversary in 2015!

Created to give shelter to those made homeless by the Blitz; we now cater for students, up-and-coming working people and those starting out in London for the first time.

Whether you are looking to make friends or take time to get to know London, with 12 sites across the city – LHA is the perfect place to start your adventure in the nation’s capital.

LHA is now a charity, but still managed by a voluntary Board of Trustees. We now have twelve large hostels providing affordable accommodation for nearly 2000 people. All have been modernised and refurbished over the past decade. In half of them, residents prepare their own food in shared kitchens. The remainder offers a catered service with large buffet-style cafeterias.

Today, the majority of our residents are young, single people studying or working in London, and live with LHA either to undertake educational courses, or if working, to give themselves time to familiarise with London, to make friends and to decide whether or not to make more private and long term arrangements for housing.

host_about:
We are a couple who enjoy living in London and have done so since the late 1980's. I am primarily a glass artist and designer and will often work from home, as my glass kiln is in a shed in the garden! As I am freelance, I also work on other projects such as interior design, and with an arts manager for a local NHS hospital.  I also volunteer with an elderly art group and at an Art Room within a primary school in NW London where art is used to support children therapeutically.  Gareth works for an interior design company, and also is a part time maths tutor, so he's the clever one!
We love to share ideas with our guests for interesting places to visit in London, especially those that are off the more well known tourist trail! Having lived in East Dulwich since 2000 we know the local area well and can make recommendations for local bars and restaurants. We really enjoy cycling as our mode of transport around London, and finding new places to explore, even after all these years of living here! We hope you will enjoy staying in our home and have a peaceful and interesting stay, and we look forward to offering our hospitality to you and hopefully being good hosts!

description:
Stylish flat, located in the heart of Shoreditch, close to major attractions, vintage markets, restaurants, clubs and East London vibe!

10mins WALKING from Liverpool St where you get the Stansted Express and the tube to Heathrow! Perfect for City professionals, travellers or Brick lane fair exhibitors.

The bedroom has a brand new king size mattress.
I also have a rear garden where to park your car/bike!

Kitchen and bathroom come fully equipped with all appliances you might need.

The space
The flat is located in the heart of East London, an incredibly vibrant area, at the ground floor of a quiet building. It has double glazed windows, wooden floor throughout, central heating and modern-ethnic decor

It has one bedroom with kingsize bed, large living room, bathroom, kitchen and rear garden.

All essentials (towels, bed linen, toilet papers, shower gel, shampoo and toothpaste) are provided

The ki
neighborhood_overview:
Shoredich has a unique atmosphere. Brick lane is the place where the terms "melting pot" originated. It's a fervent blend of several cultures, life styles, artistic spots, historical buildings, food markets, different cuisines, and cool boutiques. Expect to see the usual backgammon players at Brick lane Sunday market, enjoy a bagel from the famous bagel shops (people travel from outside London to have one :) ), get to a nice indie gig in a clothing shop, enjoy wine at vernissage, go graffiti hunting to spot the latest Bansky's and Thierry Noir's or listen to the usual buskers under the overground rail bridge. Shoreditch is an experience.
Check out my guidebook for recommendations!
host_about:
I am an East Londoner, and, for the time being, a British Academy PostDoctoral Research Fellow at Queen Mary, University of London. I have finished my PhD in Applied Linguistics and Migration Studies not long ago and worked as a Consular Officer for the Italian Ministry of Foreign Affairs and International Cooperation in the past. I am currently developing a new research project, focused on investigating identity practices in long-standing and fast-changing multicultural societies. This project involves visits to the University of Washington, Seattle, and University of British Columbia, Vancouver. So I am technically based in three countries :)

I'm interested in cultural exchange, alternative music (especially grunge, stoner, punk rock, but also psychedelic stuff, oldies, and jazz). I love books and migration literature. I am a photography amateur, self-taught. You'll find some of my shots in the flat :). I have been training as a classic ballet dancer since I was able to walk, but I enthusiastically never made it become my career.
I absolutely love travelling, food, cinema and art. I've recently become vegan (have been vegetarian for about 20 years), but I'm still flexible at times... when it comes to cheese or sushi ;).

(Please note: I can understand French, but I unable to write & I can also understand Spanish if you don't talk too fast ;) )

Peace & Love,
Alex

name: Home  for Art Lovers set in Garden
description:
The house sits in, arguably, London's most beautiful area. It is a 10 minute walk from Richmond Station and 5 minutes from Richmond Park. There is a landscaped garden. The house is suffused with light and full of art.

The space
The house is extremely bright, with light flooding in from the large landscaped garden. The walls are covered with oil paintings. The kitchen has tall windows which offer an unobstructed view of the walled garden. A large dining table is just outside the kitchen and also looks out onto the garden. The sitting room is book-lined and features a piano. Upstairs the bedrooms are comfortable with excellent mattresses. The bed in the third bedroom can be folded up as a couch; it too is extremely comfortable -- no less than the other beds. The street outside the house is very quiet. There is a parade of shops, including a delightful bakery, just one minute from the front of the house. Richmond town centre is just 10 minutes away -- s
neighborhood_overview: The neighbourhood is quiet, the neighbours kind.  The street is blocked with bollards at the bottom, so there is virtually no through traffic.  The parade of shops at the top of the road is just a one minute walk away.  There is a fantastic bakery there, a wine store and a grocery story where necessary provisions can be purchased.  London's most beautiful view (painted by Turner) is just a five minute walk from my front door.  So too is Richmond Park and the Thames River.  Richmond itself has two of London's finest theaters (the Orange Tree and Richmond Theatre) as well as two movie theatres, one specially in art films.  In town too is arguably the world's finest chocolate shop (William Curley) and various fine restaurants.  I have a list of such restaurants for guests to enjoy, as well as a small library of books about London for visitors.
host_about:
I am a professional artist -- an oil painter and the illustrator of the Japanese edition of Harry Potter.  I live and work part of the year in Princeton NJ. I have teo sons, Noah (who works in Boston in the financial sector) and Ben (a phd student at Cambridge, UK). I was widowed 9 years ago; my current partner is a professor at Princeton.   I speak Japanese fluently — also Spanish and Korean - and collect Japanese maples.

I am a keen runner -- I once ran marathons professionally (placing 3rd in the NY Marathon in 1982).  I also love cycling, singing. swimming, good literature and traveling.  

I have lived in London for 21 of the past 23 years.

I grew up in Raleigh.  My mother and older brother live in Cary.

host_about:
I am a simple person who believes that care about yourself should be more important than about the projects, the conscience and the will are not more important than the feeling and need.

So, after years in Europe (Germany, Switzerland, England...) I try to take care of my home, my studies, my body and my spirits, with the same intensity, in my small farm in Brazil.

For the house, much body work; for studies, books of Nietzsche, Spinoza, Fyodor Dostoyevsky, Franz Kafka, etc .; for my body, physical activity and to the spirits, emptiness and silence.

And even before the stricter plan, I live this place with the simplicity of to walter my plants early in the morning, to plant more trees and medicinal plants, cultivate grains and vegetables, take care of the chickens, pigs, and, in the next time, goats and horses. in the evening I'll play football with the village folk and after dinner I'll stand by the door of Mrs Nazare, to talk to the others who always appear there in the afternoon, without thinking about what to do in the next minute.

Ah! I always have time for the music of Janis Joplin, Chico Buarque, etc., play my drums and dance.

If I have guests I'm very happy if they can participate in some of my activities or if I in some of theirs. But it's not the case, I'm happy to allow the comfort of privacy and freedon necessary for a good accomodation.

Welcome to my home

The space

Furnished in light tones with terracotta flooring and and pine cabinets, the kitchen comes fully equipped with all the useful facilities for use. As you reach the first floor of the house, furnished in wooden flooring, you will find the first bedroom which is kept stylishly minimalistic with a double bed and large wardrobes allowing p
neighborhood_overview:
The beautiful expanse of Queen’s Park is a 10 minute walk from you; its wonderful 30-acre stretch of greenery has a stunning ornamental garden as well as great facilities for kids with a playground and animal farm. It also has a jogging track with exercise machines, several first class tennis courts, a par 3 pitch and putt golf course and a petanque piste. Take the family for a morning walk after breakfast or perhaps stop for a coffee in the park’s café. Wander down this neighbourhood’s Salusbury road and Chamberlayne - which was named the “hippiest street in Europe” by Vogue magazine. There are wonderful antique shops such as Howie & Belle, Niche and Circus along it, as well as a great little cocktail bar called The Shop NW10 which serves drinks in jars and bottles!

Several more restaurants and bars are dotted along Salusbury Road and the surrounding streets near Queen’s Park Station. One particularly recommended is Otsuni, an authentic Pugliese restaurant favoured by loca
host_about:
Greetings from the Veeve team!


Veeve manage the largest collection of homes to rent for short stays in London since 2011, launching in Paris in 2017. Our rental homes are predominantly privately-owned, lived-in homes in vibrant neighbourhoods. Thanks to our fully managed service, when you stay in a Veeve property you can benefit from the spaciousness, personal style and relaxed feel of a home – but with all the amenities of a hotel.


Once a booking is confirmed our Customer Service team will become your main point of contact and get in touch with you to organise your arrival at the property (including airport transfers, upon request); after which our on-the-ground management team will look after all aspects of your stay, with in-stay support available to help with any queries.


We have strict cleanliness guidelines for our cleaners and all staff who enter our properties and have reinforced existing cleaning procedures in line with official WHO, British and French government guidance.


As always, our team ensure that all properties are cleaned to a professional standard before and after each stay, with increased focus on touch-point cleaning (door handles, kitchen surfaces, kettles, taps etc.).

 All staff who enter properties will follow the below procedures:
 

- Carry and regularly use alcohol-based hand rub
- Sanitise their mobile phones 
- Focus extra attention when cleaning key touch-point areas (door handles, kitchen surfaces, kettles, taps etc.)
- Wear protective gear where appropriate
- Wash and disinfect work shoes


We might be able to arrange for property viewings, upon request, for stays of over 28 nights. 


If you have any questions, please do not hesitate to contact us and we will be sure to answer you promptly.

neighborhood_overview:
At the heart of east London's Tech City and overlooking Silicon Roundabout you will be staying in the heart of one of London's most vibrant and exciting neighbourhoods. Shoreditch and Brick Lane, Angel, Islington, the Bank of England and the financial district are all within walking distance.

Also within easy reach are a huge variety of independent coffee shops, places to eat, bars, cafes and pubs.
host_about:
Hi

I expect you'd like to know something about who you're coming to stay with.

I've been hosting on AirBnb since it's beginning in the UK in 2008. I was the fourth host in London and AirBnb has been a huge part of my life since then. I've been in Old Street for the last three years and have had a constant stream of fascinating guests who come to the diverse, creative, metropolitan hub that the ancient ward of Bunhill has become.

The Wesleys founded Methodism here, Daniel Defoe survived and wrote of the plague here. William Blake is buried here as is John Bunyan, "Pilgrims Progress".  It truly has been the home of non conformists and dissent for several centuries. It is the algorithm gods who inhabit Bunhill and Clerkenwell today. (Hidden by Airbnb) , Citymapper, (Hidden by Airbnb) and (Hidden by Airbnb) are our neighbours along with hundreds of startups - all of which are going to be "the big one".


I'm delighted  to be able to offer you rooms in this beautiful building.Behind the finest terra cotta facade In London you will be staying in one of two beautifully appointed apartments.

One is my home which I love to share with guests and the other belongs to friends who work abroad. I look after both flats, which are very close and I will be your host for your time with us.

I work as a Trade Union representative. I sing Early Music with the Festival Community Choir in  Brighton and in London. at the Charterhouse.

AirBnB makes my life possible. More than that it brings people to my door I would otherwise never meet. I enjoy their stories, their lives,  their experiences and I certainly enjoy eating and drinking with strangers and friends.

That's why I love Airbnb.

The bedroom has a balcony attached that is ideal to sit and have a coffee in the morning on. The sunset is nice as the evening sunlight casts nice shadows on the tree-lined avenue outside.

It is the perfect place to come
neighborhood_overview:
Edwardian era mansions and tree-lined streets comprise Maida Vale, a predominately residential neighbourhood in west London. It is a relaxed, safe area of London that is quiet. Small shops can be found on most streets so food or alcohol is never a problem to find quickly.

Floating homes also characterise the area—houseboats and gondolas drift through this “Little Venice” thanks to the convergence of canals near its southern border. A walk along the canal is always delightful and you can even take a waterbus to Regents Park in the summer.

Peppered with local bars and cafes, this neighbourhood has some nice places for a fashionable drink with one or two places overlooking the canal.

Favourite books:   The Alchemist, Shantaram, and Into Thin Air.

Luxury Mattress for a good nights sleep.
Once an important part of London’s river trade, Bermondsey sat derelict for several decades, until the area’s wharves were renovated in the 1980s. Now it’s a lively part of town, with some exceptionally good restaurants and coffee houses.

The space
Private use of a 1 bedroom apartment with separate lounge, kitchen and bathroom.Recently renovated Victorian Apartment. Fast Wifi, Bath and Shower, Fully equipped Kitchen.

Berm
neighborhood_overview:
Working class area of Central London, stepped in history and close to some World Class Tourist Attractions.
The name Bermondsey comes from the Anglo-Saxon phrase for “Island of Beornmund”
Beornmund was the Lord who owned the land over a thousand years ago. In the 18th Century Bermondsey became known as London’s Larder, the centre of food importing and processing, a role-played until the 1970’s. Many household brand names in the food industry had factories in Bermondsey.
Peak Frean’s biscuits, Sarson’s vinegar and Courage Breweries-earning the area its name as the Larder of London. The old industries have gradually declined leaving a legacy of fine old warehouses and industrial spaces, now home to trendy upmarket shops, restaurants, Museums, galleries and studios

-Crouch End: great restaurants, cafes, shops, bakeries, yoga studios, hairdressers, etc – it's like a little village. You can get everything here.

It also has excellent pubs!

A bustling residential area of Rotherhithe, Surrey Quays is home to the largest marina in London, leisure facilities and a convenient shopping centre in the heart of Canada Water. The first dockyard on this part of the Rotherhithe peninsula was built in 1696, a manmade network of canals, timber ponds and docks heaving with ships. Canada Water is the only freshwater lake in Docklands, once forming part of Canada Dock. Pockets of Victorian streets, pubs and some sought after 19th century warehouse conversions recall the area’s history, but the docks were almost wiped out in World War II and subsequently closed in the early 1970s. The area was redeveloped in the 1980s and the overriding feeling is modern.

description:
Welcome to our home. We are so excited to open up my property to fellow Airbnb travellers.

The space
Our beautiful home is ideally located in Kensington under 5 minutes walk away from Gloucester Road tube station. There are 3 bedrooms, making it ideal for families.

Our home is very spacious. The ground floor has a large dining room that comfortably seats 6 decorated in a beautiful traditional style. My kitchen is fantastic for those who enjoy cooking as it is fully kitted out with everything you could possibly need. The dining room and kitchen are connected but have an optional partition, so you get the best of both worlds.

On the first floor, you will find my large light living area. With a table perfect for doing work, lots of comfy seating and a TV. There is also a lovely terrace area.

The master bedroom has a massive king-size bed. All the beds are made up with fresh, luxury linens to ensure a great night’s sleep! You’ll also
neighborhood_overview:
My home is located in a beautiful area overlooking a park less than 5 minutes walk away from the tube so it is a great base for exploring London from. The desirable area of Kensington is popular for a reason. There is so much to do and see and this house could not be better placed for exploring.

You are just a 10 minutes walk away from Exhibition Road where you’ll find the Natural History Museum, Science Museum and the Victoria & Albert.

Gloucester road Road itself offers lots of fantastic eating opportunities. The Bombay Brasserie on Gloucester Road is a renowned and highly-rated Indian restaurant with a skylit conservatory. Very good food. Tendido Cero and Cambio de Tercio are sister restaurants on opposite sides of Old Brompton Road. Tendido Cero is a casual tapas bar, with delicious Spanish food and a buzzing atmosphere. Cambio de Tercio has more of a traditional restaurant feel to it and the food, also Spanish, is just as good! Worth booking.

name: (5) Elegant 1 Bed in Canary Wharf w/ River Views
description:
Welcome to my home! I’m so excited to open up my property to fellow Airbnb travelers. My beautiful one bedroom apartment, in the vibrant area of Canary Wharf, is a stylish and comfortable place to stay and has terrific transport links. You’re just a 2 minutes walk away from the nearest train.
You will enjoy the amazing river views from my flat's closed terrace.
Explore the neighbourhood and enjoy this bustling part of London.
I hope you enjoy your stay!

The space
My stylish 1 bedroom apartment is the perfect base when visiting London. Conveniently located in the exciting area of Canary Wharf and with great transport links, you’ll be right in the hub of the city but able to escape the hustle and bustle!
The living area is light and airy with a beautiful, modern design and lovely finishing touches. Relax on the sofa, hang out with your friends, make yourself at home! It’s a welcoming and inviting space where you can kick back.
The master
neighborhood_overview: Nice cafes, bars and restaurants (over 50) are in Canary Wharf and East India Quay. You can also walk along canal to the Thames (15 min walk) where you can find Gordon Ramsay restaurant The Narrow. If you are fancy a long walk or take a taxi, one of the best authentic Italian restaurants is Il Bordello. St. Katharine Docks are also not very far by taxi and have a great selection of places to eat or have a coffee while admiring beautiful yachts moored there. Or you can just hop on a tube or DLR and in half an hour you will be in Soho. There are two supermarkets less than 5 min walk - Tesco Local and Asda. There is a cash point next to Tesco store. If you like walking and the weather is good, you might like a walk by the Thames. Or you can take a Clippers if you want travel by water and see some sightseeing locations that way. Greenwich park is nearby, as well as Victoria park.

neighborhood_overview:
Ladbroke Grove is renowned for its strong connections to the arts and music industries. The annual Notting Hill Carnival takes place on Ladbroke Grove itself and the famous Portobello Market is but a mere stone's throw attracting visitors in their thousands.

Lovely Ladbroke Grove in West London has gone through a lot of changes over the years, from factory housing in the 1800s to a bohemian artist paradise in the 1960s. The British Underground scene grew up in neighbouring Notting Hill, and legendary rock star Jimmy Hendrix died here. However, this is still in the borough of Kensington and Chelsea, so it was only a matter of time before the wealthy families and media moguls moved in. Amidst the posh boutiques there are plenty of cool, creative places to check out here.

neighborhood_overview:
Mayfair is one of the most exclusive areas of central London with a mix of residential and offices and it's really not hard to see why. Some of the best shops and stores in London are on your doorstep, many of London’s top hotels are close by and the embassies and High Commissions of countless countries are based here. Mayfair is a superbly central spot for getting around the rest of this great city and is bordered to the south by Piccadilly and Green Park, to the West by Hyde Park, to the North by Oxford Street and to the East by Regent Street.

London best known sights, shopping, theatres, art galleries, museums and so much more are in the immediate area. Central London is famous for its parks and Green Park, St. James’s Park and Hyde Park (leading to Kensington Gardens) are in easy walking distance.

Hard as its bustling atmosphere now will make it to believe, Mayfair was once just a village outside London and it still retains something of the atmosphere from

My favourite food choices pretty much reflect where I love to go.  As I am not always in London, I have some friends from the industry who look after my guests and my properties for me. Nunhead is a quiet neighbourhood in Zone 2, and the house is on a residential street. neighborhood_overview: Fashionable Notting Hill is one of London's most iconic neighbourhoods. Best known as host to the world’s second biggest carnival (after Rio’s Mardi Gras) and home to the famous Portobello Road Market, Notting Hill is also a serious destination for culture buffs and those on the hunt for a quintessential London experience. On weekends throughout the year, crowds stroll the two-mile stretch of Portobello Road Market.  Colourful terraces are interspersed with antiques shops, buskers, historic pubs and clothing stalls.  Straddling the antiques and fashion markets (which are busiest on Saturdays) are the equally old-fashioned and charming produce markets, the calls of fruit and veg sellers helping give the place a Dickensian air. There’s street food of all kinds, from paella and bratwurst to crepes and churros. The markets have a grungier feel past the Westway sports centre, but it is worth persevering for the people-watching and to admire the 100m-long Portobello Wall, which features publ
host_about: I am an architectural designer living and working between Notting Hill in London and Italy. I have a particular passion for design, music and food. I am spending more of my time in Tuscany nowadays where I am rebuilding an old medieval house in a tiny hill top village in Tuscany.

neighborhood_overview:
Swiss Cottage:

Swiss Cottage is a district of the London Borough of Camden in London. It is centred on the junction of Avenue Road and Finchley Road. There are assorted shops along the length of the Finchley Road. Notable restaurants that include European, South-East Asian and Japanese cuisine. Adjoining neighbourhoods include Hampstead Village to the North East, Chalk Farm and Camden Town to the South East, Belsize Park to the East, St John's Wood to the South and West Hampstead to the West. Regent's Park is within walking distance of Swiss Cottage.

Hampstead:

Hampstead has long been known for its ridiculously gorgeous hilltop views and array of greenery to make other bits of London, well, green with envy. The jewel in the crown is, of course, Hampstead Heath’s 790 acres of woodland, playing fields, swimming ponds and meadows, with Parliament Hill providing some truly spectacular views across the city.

neighborhood_overview: Hampstead is a unique part of London - it’s only 15 minutes from the very centre of London by tube, yet feels like a quiet village. This peaceful pocket of the city is well known for its quaint Victorian architecture and population of academics, intellectuals, high-brow artists and fashionistas, as well as having one of the most amazing parks in London: the sprawling Hampstead Heath. Here you’ll find wide expanses of grassland and ancient woodland, as well as swimming ponds (where you can take a refreshing dip!), huge sports fields and facilities, playgrounds, and some of the most stunning views around from Parliament Hill. Within the Heath is the stunning visual of Kenwood House, a regency mansion that regularly features in films and on TV because of its iconic facade. What’s more, entry to the house is free to the public! The Hampstead Theatre (located close to Swiss Cottage) produces a great range of exciting plays with top acting talent, that occasionally transfer to the West End.<

You are in the heart of the haberdashery history of London, hence the names - Weavers Fields, Fashion Street - go to Beyond Retro directly opposite the flat to adorn trendy retro garb.

The fascinating Nomadic Community Garden is just 5 minutes walk just over the railway line. Here you can drink a chai and bang on a drum.

Cheshire street has many interesting shops, for ukulele, vintage clothing, tattoo, design, craft beer... you'll find it all in this area.

host_about:
Greetings from the Veeve team!


Veeve manage the largest collection of homes to rent for short stays in London since 2011, launching in Paris in 2017. Our rental homes are predominantly privately-owned, lived-in homes in vibrant neighbourhoods. Thanks to our fully managed service, when you stay in a Veeve property you can benefit from the spaciousness, personal style and relaxed feel of a home – but with all the amenities of a hotel.


Once a booking is confirmed our Customer Service team will become your main point of contact and get in touch with you to organise your arrival at the property (including airport transfers, upon request); after which our on-the-ground management team will look after all aspects of your stay, with in-stay support available to help with any queries.


We have strict cleanliness guidelines for our cleaners and all staff who enter our properties and have reinforced existing cleaning procedures in line with official WHO, British and French government guidance.


As always, our team ensure that all properties are cleaned to a professional standard before and after each stay, with increased focus on touch-point cleaning (door handles, kitchen surfaces, kettles, taps etc.).

 All staff who enter properties will follow the below procedures:
 

- Carry and regularly use alcohol-based hand rub
- Sanitise their mobile phones 
- Focus extra attention when cleaning key touch-point areas (door handles, kitchen surfaces, kettles, taps etc.)
- Wear protective gear where appropriate
- Wash and disinfect work shoes


We might be able to arrange for property viewings, upon request, for stays of over 28 nights. 


If you have any questions, please do not hesitate to contact us and we will be sure to answer you promptly.

neighborhood_overview:
Tooting in South London has developed into an uber-cool neighbourhood in recent years and lost none of its gritty charm in the process. Rubbing shoulders with perfectly pleasant yet slightly square Wimbledon, Earlsfield and Balham, Tooting is a more captivating affair, revelling in multiculturalism and originality. Its high street, which stretches between two Tube stations, is one of the best ‘curry corridors’ in the country, and contains some superb South Asian restaurants, like Dosa n Chutny and Apollo Banana Leaf.
The best shopping can be found inside eclectic Tooting Market, and quirky bars and pubs include The Castle, The Antelope and The Little Bar. The Tooting Commons create over 200 acres of green space between them, and are home to Tooting Bec Lido – the largest swimming pool in the United Kingdom.

neighborhood_overview:
Located in the heart of London, Pimlico’s brick townhouses and white stucco facades hug its well-planned streets. The bowed windows of its cafes and taverns look across genteel scenes—Anglican churches, private homes, and pristine gardens capture Pimlico’s envied restraint. Underrated and often overlooked, Pimlico augments its refined culture with casual conveniences like farmer’s markets, and easy access to high-class institutions like Millbank’s Tate Britain museum.
It’s just ten minutes’ walk to Sloane Square, a stone’s throw from Tate Britain and Buckingham Palace is within easy reach. It’s also just a brisk half an hour walk to Trafalgar Square and, cutting through St James’s Park, the route is a scenic one too.

neighborhood_overview:
About the area

The north-west London neighbourhood of Kilburn stretches out on either side of Watling Street, the ancient Anglo-Saxon road that once connected pilgrims to Canterbury and St Albans. It is now known more prosaically as the A5 and marks the boundary of two London boroughs, Brent to the west and Camden to the east. Busy and bustling Kilburn High Road has a down-to-earth-character that continues to serve its long-standing Irish and Caribbean communities well. Famous residents have included supermodel Kate Moss, actor Hugh Laurie, and comedians galore.

Walk the back streets and Kilburn reveals its intriguing history and fine historic buildings. In the 12th century a priory was established close to what is now the junction of Kilburn High Road and Belsize Road. It was dissolved by Henry VIII but lives on in local street names Priory Road and Priory Terrace, where there are fine early Victorian stucco villas.

name: Well located 2 Bed 1 Bath in Elephant & Castle
description:
Welcome to our homely apartment in Elephant and castle where you will feel comfortably at home and experience the city like a local.

The space
Our apartment comprises a living room adjective living room, dining area, a fully-equipped kitchen, 2 bedrooms and 1 bathroom.

The first stylish bedroom comes with a comfortable double bed. Our bright second bedroom features a single bed.

There is 1 bathroom in the house in total, with a toilet and a bathtub.

Guest access
You will have the whole property for yourselves during your stay.

Other things to note
Let yourself in, at your convenience, with self check-in. Enjoy our professionally cleaned and maintained property, where fluffy pillows, fresh bed linen, towels and other necessities are all provided.
neighborhood_overview:
Previously inhabited by two of Britain’s most famous exports, Charlie Chaplin and Michael Caine, the area, fondly referred to as Elephant by locals is one of London’s most interesting and colourful places.

Party animals can find the nationwide renowned Ministry of Sound club on Gaunt Street, and there a selection of other bars to compliment it nicely. On the other side of the spectrum is the Cuming Museum, situated on Walworth Road, which documents all the local Southwark history as well as the fortunes of the Cuming Family.

Elephant & Castle is in close proximity to Westminster and the South Bank. One can find a a sprawling and buzzing street market and a bizarre if not thrilling selection of Colombian cafés and bars in the local area.

neighborhood_overview: Just south of the river, Putney has the best of both worlds with quiet residential streets and green open spaces of Putney Heath, yet you are still only 15 minutes by tube from the tourist attractions and landmarks of central London, as well as world renowned sporting venues Wimbledon LTC, Fulham and Chelsea FC, The Oval and Twickenham. Putney High Street has a huge array of restaurants and shops to suit your every mood and neighbouring Fulham's upmarket boutiques and wine bars are just a short walk away over Putney Bridge. host_about:
Greetings from the Veeve team!

My name is Tom, and I work for Veeve, the largest short term property rental in London, created in 2011. We manage this collection of hand-picked apartments and houses in London, Paris and Los Angeles for their individual owners while they are away. Each property is carefully selected and offers a stylish living experience and excellent value. 

Our team of travel consultants are passionate about sharing these spaces and providing a unique experience, tailored for each guests. We have local knowledge of London, Paris and Los Angeles and we hope that our personal recommendations will help you make the most of your stay, whether you are coming for business or leisure

All our guests will be greeted personally at the property by a member of our hospitality team, and guest assistance is also provided by our customer service team between 8am - 8pm 7 days a week, should you have any requests during your stay. 

Once a booking is confirmed our customer service team will become your main point of contact and get in touch with you to organise your arrival at the property

We might be able to arrange for property viewings, upon request, for stays of over 28 nights.
  
If you have any questions please do not hesitate to contact me and I will be sure to answer them promptly.

name: Sonder | The Arts Council | Three-Bedroom Apartment near Tate Britain
description:
When picturing London, fantasies of Buckingham Palace, Big Ben, and Hyde Park tend to capture most people’s minds. And of course you want to see those landmarks — you’re in a world-class city after all! Although your chances of meeting the Royal Family are rather slim, take comfort knowing a stay at The Arts Council will provide an ere of nobility for your soul. A picturesque building where expectations are reality, feel like an heir to the throne as you rest in your expansive space. Designed with a marble aesthetic in the bathroom and extensive cabinet space in our kitchens, don’t feel guilty if a short stay extends through next month. And when you’re ready to traverse the heart of The Big Smoke, dazzling views are guaranteed, even if the weather doesn’t always agree. Just don’t forget that raincoat and phone charger.

The space
Working, relaxing, living. Our spaces have all the other essentials you need for your stay.

name: Spacious One Bed Flat with Balcony in Mile End!
description:
A wonderful one bedroom flat based on the Regents canal (Zone 2) is yours to relax and feel like home.

The flat is nicely furnished and in a safe apartment block, and has a charming balcony for you to sit and have a morning coffee. It's based on the 6th floor (accessible by a lift) and has a living area, bathroom, kitchen and dining area.

There are a couple of lovely parks nearby and lots of cafes and pubs.

Only a 7 min walk from Mile End tube station so super easy to travel around London!

The space
The flat is a modern, spacious one bedroom property with a living area, bathroom , kitchen and dining area. There is also a charming balcony for you to use.
neighborhood_overview:
The flat is based in between Mile End tube and Victoria Park which is a trendy part of town and has lots of cafes nearby. Victoria Park, which you can access by a 5 minute walk along the beautiful Regents Canal, has a wonderful Sunday food market from 10am - 4pm. Lots of people hang out in the park on sunny days. Hackney Wick is also nearby and has some nice breweries and late night bars to have drinks.

Next door to the apartment block is Mile End climbing wall if you're into bouldering?

If you take a 20 stroll East along the canal you will be at the Olympic site, a 20 minute stroll West along the canal and you will be at the very cool Broadway Market which is great on Saturday mornings for brunch and the market.

There are also pay as you ride bikes at the end of the road to help you get around London!

neighborhood_overview:
In the heart of Bromley town centre with excellent shopping and transport - yet quiet and peaceful with lots of green space around. Bromley is known as the most family friendly Borough in London with lots of things to do for everyone. Apart from the fantastic facilities on offer, Bromley is one of the safest of London's boroughs having the main regional police complex within 300m of my home.

On the High Street and within The Glades shopping centre (5 minutes' walk) you will find all the major UK and international brands as well as a swimming pool, bowling alley, indoor playcentre and gym. On Thursdays, Fridays and Saturdays there is a vibrant street market along the pedestrian mall selling fruit & vegetables, bread & cakes, hot food (the Japanese stall is my favourite) and lots more. Check out my photos for some of the activities and shops within a few minutes from our door.

neighborhood_overview:
Greenwich Village is a popular tourist location in London, with Greenwich Market hosting a large number of small boutique arts and crafts stalls and foods from around the world. The park is stunning all year round and offers some of the most incredible views of the London landscape from the hill, where you can also visit Greenwich Observatory and stand on the meridian. At the bottom of the park and through the Maritime Museum and Greenwich University grounds you can walk along the river banks or take the under-river walk path across to the Isle of Dogs and to Canary Wharf. One of my favourite walks on a sunny weekend is to start in the bottom east corner of the park, walk up the hill and across to the west, down through Cutty Sark and then back along the river.
At the top end of Greenwich Park is Blackheath Common, which is an incredible open space that is hard to beat in London. Blackheath Village is a quaint historic area piled high with cafes and restaurants and a weekend farme

name: 4 BEDROOM FAMILY HOME IN THE HEART OF BARNES
description:
We would be delighted to welcome you to stay at our lovely four bedroom family home. Family time is what makes holidays so special and our home offers the perfect setting to spend time with your loved ones.
We are located in the heart of one of London's most picturesque locations and just a short walk to Barnes High Street, local pubs, boutique shops and the River Thames.
Barnes is ideally located to explore London and the surrounding areas and has multiple transport options available.

The space
Downstairs space consists of open plan living/dining room and separate kitchen leading to the garden. There is a downstairs toilet and utility room.
Upstairs you will find four bedrooms; the master room, a single and another room with single bunk beds. There is also a children's play room or fourth bedroom and family bathroom.

Guest access
Guests have use of the whole house.
neighborhood_overview:
Barnes is a quiet, leafy village located in Greater London. It has a small village high street with 3 pubs, 2 supermarkets and other small independent boutique shops. Barnes Pond is at the end of the road, Vine Park is around the corner offering children's playground, while the River Thames is just a short stroll away.
One of our favourite local spots is the Olympic Studios which has a restaurant/cafe and cinema. This venue is steeped in history and was originally used as a recording studio for some of the world's biggest music performers!
Barnes is also known for being the home of numerous local and international film, television, music and sporting celebrities so who know's who you might bump into.
host_about:
Fun, loving family man dedicated to his wife and kids! As a family we love spending time outdoors, playing sports and doing anything that gets us out and about together as a family.
Originally from Australia, I have lived in the UK for 10 years and have many amazing memories .

name: A stylish oasis with great transport links
description:
This is a homely, peaceful, double bedroom in a stylishly decorated first-floor apartment.
It is light, airy and situated in London's historic Wandsworth Town, there is a charming village feel to the local area, which benefits from fantastic transport connections to easily access central London, Notting Hill, Victoria, Wimbeldon, Kensington and Chelsea.
The local amenities include the famous Southside shopping centre, cinemas, restaurants and traditional pubs - all within easy walking distance.

The space
The apartment has charming Victorian features (bay window, fireplaces etc) and I live in the 2 bedroom apartment with my friendly miniature dachshund dog, Twiglet.
Guests are very welcome to use the kitchen (which is fitted with a gas stove, microwave, dishwasher and oven) and to help themselves to tea and coffee.
Also available to guests is the wifi and Sky television (which is in the sitting room).
The shower is very powerful and there
neighborhood_overview:
The area is quiet and residential - an oasis away from the bustle of central London. Wandsworth Town is a charming area with cobbled streets and a village feel. There is an abundance of cafes, bars, restaurants, boutique shops and pubs. The East Hill, famous for its great food is just a five minute minute walk away and Old York Road (the historic heart of the area), which contains a high concentration of delightful neighbourhood institutions is only 8 minutes by foot.

The area is very green and has a number of parks. Spencer Park, which is charming, is a short walk away with other green areas (Wandsworth Common, Clapham Common and Battersea Park) are also easily accessible. The famous Richmond Park, home to the Royal Ballet School and wild deer, is also very convenient.

neighborhood_overview:
Travel Information
Public transport
Bethnal Green Underground Station, on the central line, is a 1-minute walk from the hotel taking you into central London in 13 minutes. Cambridge Heath Overground Station and Bethnal Green Overground Station are also very close, offering convenient connections to the National Rail network.

Seven buses and two night buses serve bus stops within a 2-minute walk of the hotel, opening up destinations in north, east and central London for our guests.

By plane
Ideally placed for both Stansted Airport and London City Airport.
The Stansted Express train takes you directly to Liverpool Street Station in 47 minutes and just one stop on the Underground to the hotel.
Alternatively hop on a National Express coach from Stansted, which drops you literally around the corner from us.

You can reach us from London City Airport in just 37 minutes, using the Docklands Light Railway (DLR) and the London Underground

host_about:
Greetings from the Veeve team!

My name is Tom, and I work for Veeve, the largest short term property rental in London, created in 2011. We manage this collection of hand-picked apartments and houses in London, Paris and Los Angeles for their individual owners while they are away. Each property is carefully selected and offers a stylish living experience and excellent value. 

Our team of travel consultants are passionate about sharing these spaces and providing a unique experience, tailored for each guests. We have local knowledge of London, Paris and Los Angeles and we hope that our personal recommendations will help you make the most of your stay, whether you are coming for business or leisure

All our guests will be greeted personally at the property by a member of our hospitality team, and guest assistance is also provided by our customer service team between 8am - 8pm 7 days a week, should you have any requests during your stay. 

Once a booking is confirmed our customer service team will become your main point of contact and get in touch with you to organise your arrival at the property

We might be able to arrange for property viewings, upon request, for stays of over 28 nights.
  
If you have any questions please do not hesitate to contact me and I will be sure to answer them promptly.

name: Contemporary 3BR in Angel with City Views (Veeve)
description:
Situated by the Regent’s Canal, this apartment offers an impressive roof terrace and space for up to 4 adults, 1 child and 1 infant. Just 20 minutes from Soho and the centre of London and just 15 minutes from King’s Cross St Pancras for connections to the Eurostar.

The space
There is an elevator up to the entrance of the apartment, which is situated on the 2nd floor of the building.

KITCHEN, DINING AND LIVING ROOM
The kitchen and dining space is contemporary in style. It includes all the amenities you will need for your stay. The room includes a dining table and seating by the window, as well as an ochre yellow sofa and armchair. There is also a television, artwork on the walls and access out to the balcony.

BALCONY
On the balcony there is a small table and chairs in green, as well as views to the surrounding area.

BATHROOM
The bathroom offers a bath, overhead shower, WC and basin, all in sleek grey tiling.
neighborhood_overview: A few minutes from this home, you can walk along the Regent’s Canal, for riverside cafes and pretty surroundings. Angel itself has plenty of shops and eateries to enjoy. Islington’s Upper street is around a 15-minute walk from the apartment- home to a whole host of wonderful boutiques, cafes, restaurants, cinemas and theatres. Visit Ottolenghi’s renowned restaurant for a taste of the Mediterranean or head to Mem and Laz Brasserie for great food and atmosphere. King’s Cross is also close by; we recommend visiting Granary Square and Coal’s Drop Yard for a taste of this area- around a 25 minute walk away. Also in the area is Old Street, Hoxton and Shoreditch- for great coffee shops, graffiti art tours and independent shops.

neighborhood_overview:
A 10-minute walk takes you straight to the heart of Brixton: a lively, multicultural area with a down-to-earth vibe. Brixton Market offers street food and vintage finds, plus clothes and produce that reflect the area’s Caribbean roots. Casual eateries serving global fare line pedestrian-friendly Brixton Village. Late-night revellers hit celebrated bars and live-music venues such as the O2 Academy Brixton for rock gigs, and Hootananny for cutting-edge sounds.

For pubs and bars, we are across the road from Brixton Jamm, a laid back venue for small music gigs. Crown & Anchor is just down the road - a brick-walled pub with infuser beer tap to increase the hops in their selection of interesting beers.

neighborhood_overview: Fashionable Notting Hill is one of London's most iconic neighbourhoods. Best known as host to the world’s second biggest carnival (after Rio’s Mardi Gras) and home to the famous Portobello Road Market, Notting Hill is also a serious destination for culture buffs and those on the hunt for a quintessential London experience. On weekends throughout the year, crowds stroll the two-mile stretch of Portobello Road Market.  Colourful terraces are interspersed with antiques shops, buskers, historic pubs and clothing stalls.  Straddling the antiques and fashion markets (which are busiest on Saturdays) are the equally old-fashioned and charming produce markets, the calls of fruit and veg sellers helping give the place a Dickensian air. There’s street food of all kinds, from paella and bratwurst to crepes and churros. The markets have a grungier feel past the Westway sports centre, but it is worth persevering for the people-watching and to admire the 100m-long Portobello Wall, which features publ

neighborhood_overview: It is a peaceful spot with a rich history - the land having once been owned for centuries by various members of Kensington gentry. host_about:
Our successful Paris & London apartment rental business began over 20 years ago with one special pied-à-terre located on the Left Bank near the Eiffel Tower. Friends and family loved staying there for the fantastic Paris views and the location – walking distance to cafés, landmarks and wonderful shops. We have a passion for sharing “la vie Parisienne”—the Parisian lifestyle—and that passion fueled the creation of our boutique vacation rental company. Our goal is to help you fall in love with Paris while discovering, exploring, tasting and savoring new sights and experiences in the incredible City of Light!

You invest a lot to come to Paris and we want you to enjoy every minute, from the moment you wake up in the morning and buy buttery warm croissants around the corner to enjoying a glass of wine and watching the sunset behind the Eiffel Tower. What makes our apartments unique is that they’re beautifully decorated, welcoming and located in the best and safest locations in Paris. description:
Welcome to our place in South London. Our house is 5 minutes walk from Vauxhall Tube Station/Vauxhall Rail Station, We're located 5 minutes from the river Thames and 20 minutes walk to The Palace of Westminster. A longer walk or short bus/tube ride will take you to Victoria, the gateway to the West End of London including Buckingham Palace, Trafalgar Square and beyond. To the South we are close to vibrant Brixton, Clapham and Peckham.

The space
Our house is eclectic and individual, reflecting our tastes and personalities. We like to think of it as an Insta dream and we've created our own Insta for the space @southwest_8

name: Family room with ensuite in Bloomsbury hotel.
description:
This listing is for a private room with 1 double & 2 single beds (sometimes a bunkbed) & private bathroom, no breakfast.

The St Athans Hotel is a proudly simple, family-run, green hotel in Bloomsbury, central London - just walking distance from many famous landmarks, museums, theatres and shops. Based in historic Grade II listed Georgian Townhouses, we offer great value for money and a friendly service - providing a comfortable home from home in a convenient location.

The space
Ours is a simple, family-run, affordable space in central London. What we lack in amenities we try make up for in service. It's a quirky place with grand staircases, wonky walls, exposed pipes, full of original artwork from one of the owners and dotted with family memorabilia and presents from guests around the world. We aim to be a home from home, rather than a flash hotel.

Each room is individually decorated - has a wash basin, somewhere to hang your clothes, a com
neighborhood_overview: Bloomsbury is by far the best place to stay in London, even if we do say so ourselves :) It's right in the centre of the city but in a quiet, leafy neighbourhood famous for its illustrious former residents. You can walk everywhere worth walking to - we're down the road from 3 mainline stations and 4 Underground station, the British Museum, British Library, Covent Garden, West End etc ..... It's mostly safe around here (and in London in general) but being in the centre of a city of 8 million you still need to keep your wits about you.

neighborhood_overview: With its unpretentious salt of the earth vibe, coupled with a cheery mix of green space, lively high streets and the new openings arriving thick and fast, Tooting has plenty to recommend it. It’s slightly quieter than neighbouring Balham and Streatham and has become a favourite location for young professionals and families who are looking for their own bit of space. Tooting is known for its lido, which is the largest of its kind in the UK, and for the wide green expanses of the Tooting Commons. There is also a vibrant and ever expanding bar and restaurant scene and, certainly south of the river, this is the place to find authentic south Asian cuisine. Transport to and from anywhere in Tooting is easy: it has two Tube stations, alongside rail and bus connections, and journey times can be under half an hour into central London.

The neighbourhood is one of the most exciting and fast growing cultural and business districts in the British capital. Over two thousand years of history have given rise to the area’s continuing link to commerce and its undeniable creative and pioneering spirit.

With award-winning restaurants, critically acclaimed galleries and independent boutiques, the London Bridge neighbourhood continues to grow in business, culture, the arts and leisure amenities.

As new businesses and developments arrive in the capital, they seamlessly fit into a city rich in history and achievement. The wifi is fast should you be working from home this is the perfect sp
neighborhood_overview:
Shepherd’s Bush is a really exciting area of London - it has so much character with plenty to explore. When we resume to normality shopping is available at the huge Westfield centre.
The big shopping centre locally is Westfield, a huge and modern centre with everything including food and entertainment.

The Eagle is a popular pub with a lively atmosphere and a large garden where you can enjoy a jug of Pimms in the summer, or sit by the log fire in the colder months. A lovely place to enjoy an English ale. The food is good too.
The Shepherd’s Bush Market, open Monday to Saturday (9am-6pm), is vibrant and bustling. With everything from falafels to dumplings, fabrics to scarves, and fresh fruit and vegetables, this traditional local market is definitely worth exploring.
You are also just next-door to the fun area of Notting Hill (20 mins by tube, 30 min walk) where you can wander to Portobello Road and discover vintage clothes at the weekend market there.

The space
Your bright, modern ensuite room has a comfortable bed with a private shower room with sink and toilet. There is a large desk area with an office chair, ideal if you have some work to do on the laptop using the free WiFi. You’ll find lots of general storage space in the room and a wardrobe as well. neighborhood_overview:
The residence is ideally situated south of the River Thames between Borough and Southwark underground stations.

The nearest restaurant is The Laughing Gravy which serves seasonal modern British cuisine in an informal space with a skylight ceiling and exposed brick walls, it’s only a 5 minute walk. A little further afield but for lots of choice of restaurants of all styles head toward London Bridge, en-route you can find Borough Market after about 14 minutes walking. Here there is food a plenty from around the world and home!

Eating In
Pizza 2 Go and Chinese Canteen are both a 9 minute walk if you fancy some great takeaway food to bring home. If you want to make use of your shared kitchen then you can buy fresh produce to cook up yourself at Tesco Express, just 6 minutes walk away.

name: Beautiful loft apartment overlooking pretty park
description:
A beautiful, modern one bedroom apartment on the top floor of our Edwardian house in Lewisham, South East London. Little but perfectly formed, it has everything you could need including a fully equipped kitchen with dishwasher, high speed internet and a cosy bedroom with luxury king sized bed. We are directly opposite a lovely park which is perfect for a morning stroll and are close to two train stations which will have you in London Bridge in a little as 10 minutes, and Charing Cross in 17

The space
We built the apartment so that we had somewhere to stay whilst we were renovating the rest of our house, and to this day it’s one of our favourite parts of the property. Light, airy, modern, quiet and super comfortable. We look into a beautiful park full of mature trees so the birdsong in the morning is incredible

Guest access
The apartment itself is totally private with its own lockable front door. Please note, access is through our house-thro
neighborhood_overview:
We’re equidistant (about 10 mins walk to each) between Ladywell and Hither Green-each has pretty cafés, shops and a good pub. The Station pub in Hither Green Is a firm favourite with a good menu and range of beers.

Two miles away, so a longer walk or very short Uber/bus ride is Blackheath which is one of the most beautiful parts of London with its heath for walking and village like centre for shopping, eating and drinking.

Just past there is Greenwich Park, which is simply stunning especially late afternoon as the sun is setting over the city, with amazing views from the Royal Observatory.

Brockley is very cool and very close and both Dulwich and Forest Hill are easily reachable two.

The space

GROUND FLOOR

KITCHEN
The kitchen is a beautiful, spacious room, full of light with fresh white interiors, and doors opening onto the garden. Wood flooring, bay windows and a cottage-style dining table create a vintage, homely feel, whilst smart grey units and sleek marble counters offer a stylish modern uplift. There is a large kitchen island with a sink and 2 bar stools, and a dining table with 5 chairs. Additional seating is offered by a cushy window sofa and a high chair is available upon request. Special features include a large doubl
neighborhood_overview: Claphams impressive night-life is probably one of the main draws for the many young professionals who live here — the highstreet is rarely, if ever, empty on the weekends. But Clapham is not just a party-hot spot, it’s also a wonderfully pretty south London neighbourhood, with pristine Georgian-era townhouses, cosy pubs and lush stretches of greenery. The vast expanse of Clapham Common is a favourite spot for locals to lounge in the summer months, and several fabulous brunch spots skirt the out-edges of the Common,: try The Jam Tree or Metro Garden if you’re feeling peckish.
host_about:
Greetings from the Veeve team!


Veeve manage the largest collection of homes to rent for short stays in London since 2011, launching in Paris in 2017. Our rental homes are predominantly privately-owned, lived-in homes in vibrant neighbourhoods. Thanks to our fully managed service, when you stay in a Veeve property you can benefit from the spaciousness, personal style and relaxed feel of a home – but with all the amenities of a hotel.


Once a booking is confirmed our Customer Service team will become your main point of contact and get in touch with you to organise your arrival at the property (including airport transfers, upon request); after which our on-the-ground management team will look after all aspects of your stay, with in-stay support available to help with any queries.


We have strict cleanliness guidelines for our cleaners and all staff who enter our properties and have reinforced existing cleaning procedures in line with official WHO, British and French government guidance.


As always, our team ensure that all properties are cleaned to a professional standard before and after each stay, with increased focus on touch-point cleaning (door handles, kitchen surfaces, kettles, taps etc.).

 All staff who enter properties will follow the below procedures:
 

- Carry and regularly use alcohol-based hand rub
- Sanitise their mobile phones 
- Focus extra attention when cleaning key touch-point areas (door handles, kitchen surfaces, kettles, taps etc.)
- Wear protective gear where appropriate
- Wash and disinfect work shoes


We might be able to arrange for property viewings, upon request, for stays of over 28 nights. 


If you have any questions, please do not hesitate to contact us and we will be sure to answer you promptly.

neighborhood_overview:
With an 800-year-old history, the City of London has a wealth of museums, galleries, green spaces, bars, restaurants, churches and shops.

The City of London is home to some of London’s most popular attractions, including Tower Bridge, The Tower of London, St Paul’s Cathedral and the Museum of London. Notable buildings in the area include the Gherkin, 30 St Mary Axe and The Cheesegrater at 122 Leadenhall Street. It’s a great place to dine out, as The City is crammed full of upscale eateries and celebrity chef restaurants. If you have cash to splash, go shopping at the historic Leadenhall Market or Old Spitalfields Market.

name: Gorgeous, homely, stylish 1 bed flat
description:
Kick back and relax in this lovely, spacious home with everything you could possibly need! Great neighbourhood and links to other parts fo the city. Wonderful, helpful neighbours, local grocery stores with delicious produce, well priced. This is my home so it has a whole host of personal touches. I have been an air bnb host before, at a different place - see reviews. I love this place even more! It has really lovely features, like beautiful wooden floors and tiled bathroom.

The space
The flat is in a Victorian house which has been split into two so, although it's a flat, it is spacious and has lovely high ceilings. The front door is thick and heavy so great for security. You enter the flat through the living room where there is a bay window so lots of light. there's a 3 seater sofa - very comfy - and an arm chair. There are lots of blankets for snuggling up, too. The bedroom is a spacious double and has drawers for storage. Under the bed is more linen and towels
neighborhood_overview:
The flat is close to everything you might need! There are lots of grocery shops within a minutes walk which are well priced and sell a range of food and lots of other things you might need. There is a large supermarket about 20 minutes walk away for anything else. I am close to the popular Walthamstow village and Clapton - both really fun areas with great restaurants and bars.
One of the things I love most about my area is the huge amount of green space, despite it being urban. Wanstead Flats are a bus ride away where it's pretty rugged and wild. Epping Forest is about 20 minutes away by car/taxi if you want something a bit bigger to walk through. There's lots of little parks close by, too. One of my personal favourites is Hackney Marshes where you can wander along the canal and pop into buzzing bars and cafes along the way.
host_about: I'm a teacher working in London. I’m active; I love going for runs, doing yoga and walking. I really enjoy cooking and eating out.
